<h1>Tutorial 11. Sewing the Underskirts.&nbsp; Installing a Zipper into the Top Skirt.&nbsp; Joining All Skirt Layers.</h1>
<p><strong>It is time to sew the underskirts. </strong>This is done by gathering all strips along one edge with a 2:1 gathering ratio. I do it with a special ruffler presser foot.</p>
<p><strong>I gather the first-tier stripe from 150cm down to 70cm. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image002.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p>Then, <strong>I join the two strips for the second tier</strong> without changing the presser foot.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image004.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I continue gathering the 3m long stripe down to 1.5m.&nbsp; </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image006.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p>And so it goes: <strong>first I sew the stripes together and then gather them. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image008.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Next, I need to join the tiers. </strong></p>
<p>I sew the second tier to the first one. This ruffle is already 3m long.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image010.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Then I sew in place the yellow ruffle </strong>which was gathered from 6m down to 3m.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image012.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p>And then, <strong>I sew together the 12m long chiffon ruffle folded in half.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image014.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I gather this 12m of chiffon down to 6m: </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image016.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Here is what it looks like: </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image018.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Then I serge the edge of the full sweep skirt: </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image020.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>And I serge the edges of all seams on all tiers:&nbsp; </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image022.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I sew a 6m long chiffon ruffle to the yellow tier: </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image024.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>And I serge the edges of the seam: </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image026.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I also serge the edges of the central back seam.</strong> The seam allowances of all tier seams must be directed upwards.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image028.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I serge the other edge of the same seam:&nbsp; </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image030.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p>And then <strong>I sew a strengthening seam along the seam allowance of the bottom chiffon ruffle. </strong>It secured the seam allowance in the upward position.</p>
<p>The ruffle settles better this way.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image032.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I sew the central seam at the back of the skirt leaving about 18cm open for a closure area.&nbsp; </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image034.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I give a frame-like finish to this area.</strong> I won't sew a zipper in there because it will be installed in the full sweep skirt.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image036.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>This is our bright and pretty underskirt!&nbsp; </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image038.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p>I have realized that one underskirt does not give enough volume to the full sweep skirt. I repeat the entire cutting process <strong>and sew another underskirt that is just the same as the first one.</strong></p>
<p>Then, <strong>I gather the top edge of the full sweep skirt and sew the central back seam.</strong> Remember to compare the length of the slit with the length of the zipper first. I have decided to sew a regular seam and not a dart.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image040.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I sew in a regular zipper: </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image042.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I turn the hem of the full sweep skirt by about 1cm and sew along: </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image044.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I put the three skirts together: </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image046.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>And I join them in the closure area. </strong>I fold the underskirts in half and align their centre points with the central notch on the full sweep skirt.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image048.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p>And <strong>I re-distribute the fabric evenly between the sides, the back, and the front. </strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image050.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Here is the result!</strong> All I need to do is press the seam at the bottom of the full sweep skirt and add a waistband.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Fancy%20Dresses%20for%20girls/12%20yo/Tutorial%2011.files/image052.jpg" alt=""></p>

</div> <!-- Itemprop END: articleBody -->
